data.title: Kris Jenner, 68, sets date for wedding to much younger Corey Gamble, 43
data.meta_description: Kris Jenner has been married twice before, but it seems a recent health scare has made her consider walking down the aisle for a third time with her longtime boyfriend Corey Gamble.
data.text:
The Kardashians Season 5: Official trailer

Kris Jenner has dropped a hint that wedding bells might be in her future, revealing she's not opposed to the idea of marrying Corey Gamble.

The 68-year-old momager, who has been through two divorces, had previously declared no intention to remarry, but a health scare seems to have shifted her perspective.

After being advised to undergo an oophorectomy due to a tumor discovery, Kris faced another daunting medical recommendation.

Kim Kardashian admits 'tragic' and sudden health effect of ageing at 43

Kris Jenner sparks health concerns after 'swollen' hands spotted in new photos

During an intimate conversation with friends Kathy Hilton and Faye Resnick on The Kardashians, Kris shared her upcoming surgery plans: "Tomorrow morning at six o'clock in the morning, I'm gonna have a hysterectomy."

She elaborated on the escalation of her medical situation, saying: "It started out as just getting some ovaries removed and then today I got a phone call.

"Dr A, she goes, 'Listen, I really think the best thing for you is to remove the whole thing, do the complete hysterectomy and not give anything a chance to grow anywhere, so no ovarian cancer'."

Her friends offered their unwavering support, even humorously misinterpreting her serious news for a marriage announcement.

Kathy quipped: "I thought you were gonna tell me you're getting married!"

To which Kris responded with a laugh: "I mean, not right this very second."

Kathy humorously remarked, "I thought you were gonna say, 'At six in the morning...' like, that's a little early for me to be dressed. What are we wearing? " Kris then shared her wish for her friends to stand with her as bridesmaids.

"Dressed and ready to go as a bridesmaid," Kris specified. Kathy expressed her excitement about the idea, responding, "As a bridesmaid, for sure."

Kris confirmed their future roles by saying, "I mean, you guys could totally be bridesmaids when I get married. Okay, so maybe when I'm 70."

Should Kris tie the knot with Corey, it wouldn't mark her debut down the aisle.

Her marriage to Robert Kardashian lasted 13 years until an affair with Todd Waterman came to light, ending their union.

She went on to marry Caitlyn Jenner, formerly known as Bruce Jenner, in 1991, but they parted ways in 2013.
